   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Message Twelve The New Jerusalem</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>the Destination of the Flowing Triune God Scripture Reading: Gen 2:10-12; Psa 36:8-9; 46:4;</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>John 4:14b; 2 Cor 13:14; Rev 22:1 The New Jerusalem is the destination of the flowing Triune God: The water that I will give him will become in him a fountain of water gushing up into eternal life John 4:14b: The Triune God flows in the Divine Trinity in three stages: The Father is the fountain, the Son is the spring, and the Spirit is the river.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>This flowing Triune God is into eternal life : The New Jerusalem is the totality of the eternal life; thus, into eternal life means into the New Jerusalem.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Into speaks of the destination; into means issuing in, to be, or to become ; into the New Jerusalem means to become the New Jerusalem.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Father as the fountain, the Son as the spring, and the Spirit as the river flow into us and with us into the New Jerusalem to be the New Jerusalem.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The Father as the fountain, the Son as the spring, and the Spirit as the river all take the New Jerusalem as Their eternal goal.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In the beginning, in eternity past, was the Word, who was God; in eternity future, the Word becomes the New Jerusalem John 1:1; 4:14b; Rev 21:10.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The triune, eternal God becomes the New Jerusalem incorporated with all of us by the divine speaking, divine spreading, divine dispensing, of Himself into us as the flowing Triune God for our enjoyment to be our eternal blessing for His eternal glory Rev 22:1-2, 17; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Num 6:22-27; 2 Cor 13:14.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The New Jerusalem is the destination of the line of life throughout the Bible, and the lake of fire is the destination of the line of knowledge Gen 2:8-9: At the end of the Bible we have two results, two consummations a city of living water Rev 22:1 and a lake of burning fire 20:10, 14-15; 21:8 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The river of water for reviving and watering proceeds out of the throne of God and will flow all positive things into the New Jerusalem 22:1.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The stream of fire for judging issues out of the throne of God and will sweep all negative things into the lake of fire Dan 7:9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>We need to exercise our spirit to enjoy the flowing Triune God within us, in the midst of an environment of heat and pressure, so that we may be transformed into precious materials for us to become the New Jerusalem Gen 2:10-12; 1 Cor 3:12; Rev 21:18-21; John 4:14b, 24: The river of water of life is the flowing out of the Triune God the Spirit as the ultimate consummation of the processed Triune God reaching His redeemed people for their enjoyment Rev 22:1; Psa 36:8-9; 46:4: God s intention in His economy is to be the fountain, the source, of living waters to satisfy His chosen people for their enjoyment, with the goal of producing the Body of Christ, consummating in the New Jerusalem as God s fullness for His expression Jer 2:13; Lam 3:22-24.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Our drinking of the one Spirit makes us members of the Body, builds us up as the Body, and prepares us to be the bride of Christ 1 Cor 12:13; Rev 22:17.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>By drinking the living water, we become the New Jerusalem, the totality of the eternal life, the destination of the flowing Triune God John 4:14b.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>As believers in Christ, we need to drink and flow the water of life John 4:10, 14; 7:37-39; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Prov 11:25: To drink the water of life, there is the need of thirst Exo 17:3a; Psa 42:1; John 7:37; Rev 21:6.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>We need to come to the Lord and ask Him to give us the living water John 7:37; Rev 22:17; John 4:10.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>We need to contact God the Spirit in our human spirit and in truthfulness John 4:23-24; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Jude 19-21.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>We need to joyously draw water from the springs of salvation by speaking to the Lord, by the Lord, for the Lord, in the Lord, and with the Lord John 19:34; 1 Cor 10:4; Exo 17:6; Num 20:8; Isa 12:2-6: We need to practice speaking with the Lord constantly Phil 4:6-7, 12.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>We need to confess our sins John 4:15-18; 1 John 1:9; Num 21:16-18.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>We need to praise the Lord Phil 4:4; Heb 13:15; Psa 119:164.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>We need to thank the Lord Eph 5:18, 20.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>We need to call on the name of the Lord Acts 2:21; 1 Cor 12:13, 3; 1 Thes 5:17; 1 Cor 1:2; Judg.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>15:18-19; Lam 3:55-56.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>We need to sing to the Lord Eph 5:18b-19; 1 Kings 6:7; 1 Chron 6:31-32; 2 Chron 20:21-22.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>We need to preach the gospel, making known to others what Christ has accomplished Rom 1:16; John 4:32-34.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>We need to function in the meetings of the church 1 Cor 14:4b, 26.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>We need to be identified with the smitten Christ Exo 17:6; John 7:38; S. S. 2:8-9, 14; Phil 3:10; Heb 12:2.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>We need to give the Lord the preeminence in our being Rev 22:1; Col 1:18b.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>We need to do everything in the inner flow of the divine life, the fellowship of the divine life, according to the divine nature 1 John 1:3; Rev 22:1; Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>47:1; 2 Pet 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>We need to work with the Lord in the divine stream, the stream of the work of God, the fellowship, the flow, of the divine life for us to build the New Jerusalem Rev 22:1-2; John 7:37-39: To have fellowship with the Triune God in the apostles fellowship is to put aside our private interests and to join with the apostles and the Triune God for the carrying out of God s purpose 1 John 1:3.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>The flowing of the divine life, which started on the day of Pentecost and has been flowing throughout all the generations to this day, is just one stream cf.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Acts 15:39-41.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Wherever the stream of the divine life is, precious materials will be produced for God s building Gen 2:10-12.</S>
   </TEXT>
